FBIS3-54759 "drsov001_b_94032" FBIS-SOV-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Yeltsin Creates Central Command for Border Troops LD3012144193 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1334 GMT 30 Dec 93 LD3012144193 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Roman Zadunayskiy] [Text] Moscow, 30 December -- Today, Russian President Boris Yeltsin signed an edict "On the formation of the Federal Border Service-Central Command of the Russian border troops." The ITAR-TASS correspondent learned this from Colonel Yevgeniy Znamenskiy, deputy head of the press office of the Russian border troops. The edict has been issued in connection with the dismantling of the Russian Ministry of Security and in order to ensure continuity of command of the Russian border troops. The representative of the press office has also reported that under the decree, the Federal Border Service-Central Command of the Russian border troops is to a have a status equivalent to that of a Federal ministry and to operate in direct subordination to the Russian president and government. Colonel General Andrey Nikolayev has been appointed the commander in chief of Russia's border troops.
